		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston&#44; S. C.</placeName> <date>April 8. 1853</date>.</p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#33; Will you be pleased to<lb/> send me regularly the Occident and forward your bill<lb/> to your agent in this city. &#40;beginning with No 1 of Vol. XI.&#41;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">A friend of mine presented me this week<lb/> with a series of the Occident&#44; complete&#44; with the exception<lb/> of the 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> vol. the 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> number of which is lost. You would<lb/> therefore confer a great favor upon me&#44; if you could send<lb/> me&#44; by mail&#44; this No 1 of Vol. VI as I am very<lb/> anxious to have my series of the O. complete.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I embrace this opportunity&#44; to inform you&#44;<lb/> as an old friend&#44; of my being engaged to be married to<lb/> <persName>Miss Rachel Ottolengui</persName>&#44; daughter of the late <persName>Abraham<lb/> Ottolengui</persName> of this city.</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">I remain with my best regards</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">Yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">most respectfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Dr M Mayer</persName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>371 Walnut St.</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
          
        </body>
